Name: Alex
Video_Title: DeMISTifying Electronic Nicotine Delivery Systems (ENDS) and Their Effects on Hormones
Description:
this is a short description of how vapes, e-cigs, and juuls, known as electronic nicotine delivery systems (ends), can affect the body through an imbalance of hormones, specifically dopamine and insulin. ends can be broken down into active ingredients, such as nicotine and flavoring, and filler ingredients, such as propylene glycol, glycerol, and preservatives like formaldehyde. filler ingredients have other effects on the body not covered by the video. the active ingredients and some filler ingredients are absorbed by the lungs and travel through the blood stream to the brain. in the brain, nicotine, one of the common active ingredients, increases dopamine production and release. additionally, some flavorings have been shown to increase dopamine production, even in the absence of nicotine. in the brain, dopamine functions in cognition and mood. it is normally released after satisfying activities and is the primary factor behind the addictive nature of nicotine. outside of the brain, dopamine has been shown to increase urination through a decrease in salt absorption in the kidneys. additionally, dopamine has been shown to mimic diabetes mellitus by decreasing insulin production in the pancreas. insulin functions by increasing the transport of sugar from the bloodstream into cells. from there, the sugar can be made into atp for energy. thus, nicotine and some flavorings in ends can cause deleterious effects in the body through significant hormone imbalance.

special thanks to daelyn doughty for filming and editing and to the alleluia community school for allowing me to film in their beautiful auditorium.

resources consulted:
alasmari f, crotty alexander le, hammad am, bojanowski cm, moshensky a, sari y. 2019. effects of chronic inhalation of electronic cigarette vapor containing nicotine on neurotransmitters in the frontal cortex and striatum of c57bl/6 mice. front pharmacol. 10:885.

arane k, goldman rd. 2016. electronic cigarettes and adolescents. can fam physician. 62(11):897-898.

arnold c. 2014. vaping and health: what do we know about e-cigarettes? environ health perspect. 122(9):a244-249.

avelar aj, akers at, baumgard zj, cooper sy, casinelli gp, henderson bj. 2019. why flavored vape products may be attractive: green apple tobacco flavor elicits reward-related behavior, upregulates nachrs on vta dopamine neurons, and alters midbrain dopamine and gaba neuron function. neuropharmacology. 158:107729.

beauval n, antherieu s, soyez m, gengler n, grova n, howsam m, hardy em, fischer m, appenzeller bmr, goossens jf et al. 2017. chemical evaluation of electronic cigarettes: multicomponent analysis of liquid refills and their corresponding aerosols. j anal toxicol. 41(8):670-678.

burstyn i. 2014. peering through the mist: systematic review of what the chemistry of contaminants in electronic cigarettes tells us about health risks. bmc public health. 14:18.

choi dw, jeon j, lee sa, han kt, park ec, jang si. 2018. association between smoking behavior patterns and glycated hemoglobin levels in a general population. int j environ res public health. 15(10).

dawkins l, cox s, goniewicz m, mcrobbie h, kimber c, doig m, kosmider l. 2018. 'real-world' compensatory behaviour with low nicotine concentration e-liquid: subjective effects and nicotine, acrolein and formaldehyde exposure. addiction. 113(10):1874-1882.

el-hage r, el-hellani a, salman r, talih s, shihadeh a, saliba na. 2018. fate of pyrazines in the flavored liquids of e-cigarettes. aerosol sci technol. 52(4):377-384.

liedtke wb, mckinley mj, walker ll, zhang h, pfenning ar, drago j, hochendoner sj, hilton dl, lawrence aj, denton da. 2011. relation of addiction genes to hypothalamic gene changes subserving genesis and gratification of a classic instinct, sodium appetite. proc natl acad sci u s a. 108(30):12509-12514.

rubi b, maechler p. 2010. minireview: new roles for peripheral dopamine on metabolic control and tumor growth: let's seek the balance. endocrinology. 151(12):5570-5581.

Name: Alex
Video_Title: Wismec R40 Pod Mod Review | Vape UK
Description:
#wismec #wismecr40 #vapeproud

this video jonny gets a first look at the wismec r40. 

the wismec r40 joins the r80 in wismec’s duo of pod mods. it’s the perfect option for vapers who prefer an integrated battery. 

the integrated battery has a 1700mah capacity and the kit utilizes usb-c fast charge technology to dramatically reduce downtime. 

the wismec r40 has variable wattage from 1 – 40w and can be adjusted easily using the two-button system. the kit can also be set to smart mode. when in smart mode, the r40 will detect the resistance of the atomizer head which is fitted and automatically adjust the wattage setting to the optimum level. 

the device is nice and compact and retains a similar shape to the r80, based on the iconic reuleaux triangle. it’s a phenomenal looking kit with dazzling grill panels, available in ruby, sapphire, black, silver and black and silver. 

adding to the stunning looks of the r40 is a crystal clear 0.96 inch colour screen. this interface displays all key information including remaining battery life, atomizer resistance and your current wattage setting.
recessed within the body of the r40 is the pod cartridge. this pod is filled at the side by removing the rubber bung. it utilizes the wv range of atomizer heads, which use a push fit mechanism. airflow can be adjusted at the base of the atomizer head to suit your preferences.

the r40 comes fitted with the wv-m 0.3ohm atomizer head for use at higher powers, resulting in great vapour production. the wv01 0.8ohm atomizer comes as a spare for vapers who prefer lower powers while retaining vivid flavours and decent vapour production. 

the wismec r40 is the perfect device for you if you love creating large clouds from a really slick looking device which will stand the test of time!

Video_Title: What is disposable income?
Description: this study video looks at a key macroeconomic indicator - the level of household disposable income. ​disposable income is the amount of money that individuals and families have available for spending or saving after they have paid their direct taxes and received any state welfare benefits. direct taxes include income tax, national insurance and (local) council tax.

Video_Title: A Vaping-Related Illness Has Turned Deadly, Here’s What You Need to Know
Description:
vaping has soared in popularity, with now more than 40 million users worldwide. but an unexplained respiratory illness has swept the u.s. in recent weeks, and many health investigators suspect that vaping might be to blame.
» subscribe to seeker!http://bit.ly/subscribeseeker
» watch more elements! http://bit.ly/elementsplaylist 

vapes, vape pens, e-cigarettes—whatever you want to call them—are essentially just battery-powered devices that heat a liquid into a vapor that can be inhaled. the vapor can contain flavoring and nicotine, but marijuana and hash oil are often used, too.

in recent weeks, reports of a mysterious respiratory illness have taken the u.s. by storm, one that’s affected at least 380 patients and turned fatal for seven.  as health investigators begin to look into the issue, a common thread seems to be emerging; vaping.  

but medical studies are still in the preliminary stages, and there remains a severe lack of information surrounding the health effects of vaping. 

now, with at least 380 confirmed cases of the mysterious respiratory illness in the u.s., the public is looking for answers. 

the first reported vaping-related death occurred in august 2019 in illinois, and since then, six vaping-related deaths have been reported in california, indiana, kansas, minnesota, and oregon.

seeker reached out to dr. david christiani, a pulmonologist and molecular epidemiologist who collated and summarized the most recent major medical case studies on the vaping-related epidemic for the new england journal of medicine.

learn more about what we know, don’t know, and what steps are being taken with regard to vapes and the impacts vaping could have on one’s health on this episode of elements. 

#vapingdeaths #vapes #ecigarettes #nicotine #thc #cannabis

“the state department of health said in a news release that “very high levels” of the compound had been found in 13 samples from eight of 34 patients who have gotten ill in new york. the samples were analyzed as part of an investigation by the wadsworth center, a state laboratory.”
